Class CallRenderer

java.lang.Object
  org.scilab.modules.renderer.CallRenderer

public final class CallRenderer
extends java.lang.Object

This is a static class to access the renderer module directly from C/C++ code through JNI. See SCI/modules/renderer/src/jni/renderer.giws.xml for other details.

get2dViewCoordinates

public static double[] get2dViewCoordinates(java.lang.String id,
                                            double[] coords)
Computes and returns the coordinates of a point projected onto the default 2d view plane. The obtained coordinates correspond to the point's object coordinates in the default 2d view coordinate frame (the point's position being fixed in window coordinates). The projected point's z coordinate is set to 0, as only x and y are relevant.

Parameters:
id - the identifier of the Axes object.
coords - the input object coordinates (3-element array).
Returns:
the 2d view coordinates (3-element array).

getPixelFrom2dViewCoordinates

public static double[] getPixelFrom2dViewCoordinates(java.lang.String id,
                                                     double[] coords)
Computes and returns the pixel coordinates from a point's coordinates expressed in the default 2d view coordinate frame, using the given Axes. The returned pixel coordinates are expressed in the AWT's 2d coordinate frame.

Parameters:
id - the Axes' identifier.
coords - the 2d view coordinates (3-element array: x, y, z).
Returns:
the pixel coordinates (2-element array: x, y).

get2dViewFromPixelCoordinates

public static double[] get2dViewFromPixelCoordinates(java.lang.String id,
                                                     double[] coords)
Computes and returns the coordinates of a point projected onto the default 2d view plane from its pixel coordinates, using the given Axes. The pixel coordinates are expressed in the AWT's 2d coordinate frame. The returned point's z component is set to 0, as we only have x and y as an input.

Parameters:
id - the Axes' identifier.
coords - the pixel coordinates (2-element array: x, y).
Returns:
the 2d view coordinates (3-element array: x, y, z).

getViewingArea

public static double[] getViewingArea(java.lang.String id)
Computes and returns the viewing area of the Axes object given by the identifier. The viewing area is defined by its upper-left corner and its dimensions, all values are in pixels. It is expressed in the AWT's 2d coordinate frame.

Parameters:
id - the Axes' identifier.
Returns:
the Axes' viewing area (4-element array: x, y, width, height).
